<br>
The problem in PoN wasn't that the consorts dropped spectral parchments. Those mobs don't spawn too quickly and are a decent challenge (and there's only 2 besides). The problem was they were just about the only mobs outside HoH (excluding higher tier zones than HoH of course) that dropped spectrals (I'd say only, but I haven't fought enough in Plane of Storms to know for sure).<br>
<br>
As for Wezloc's comment about not intending to get our spells withing 2 weeks. Well, until PoP, I never spent 2 weeks in a level without having all my spells. Only exception has been level 60 pet heal, it's the only pre-PoP spell I do not have. And for the most part I had all my spells prior to levelling. Yes, I expect to have my spells in a reasonable time frame after gaining a level, preferablly before I am ready to hit the next level.<br>
<br>
And why is there always one idiot who needs to compare spells to melee equipment. They are not the same thing. Spells are to casters what bash, kick, taunt, and disciplines are to melee classes. Might have been a time that would have been a more legitimate argument (when caster loot basiclly sucked), but with all the new foci, flowing thought items, and clicky items for casters now available, that logic is out of date. Loot is now more important for casters, don't believe me ? Parse the differance between a caster with no flowing thought, no clicky items, and only summoned foci versus a caster with VT foci/clickies and FT15.<br>
<br>
Anyways, back to the topic. This nerf sucked, it sucked for everyone. Let's hope this is undone, and let's further hope we see more mobs dropping the parchments we all need.<br>
