<br>
At the level they can be scribed, their quite good. The current crop of Ancient spells are level 60. There's no reason level 61-65 Ancient spells could not be added that are superior to their normal counterparts.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As for people expecting to have all their spells as soon as they level, or before they do... Well, the only people who really should expect that are people in FoH, AL, Triton,.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Oh ? why is that now ? I disagree with this sentiment and do not believe we should be at the mercy of larger guilds to obtain our spells.  We should be able to earn them ourselves, and until recently, we could. Placing them past tier 2 zones basiclly puts them beyond most people's reach. Even if you can get a key/flag to those zones, your actual chances of finding a group there is next to nil as the majority of people there will be of the same guild and not inclined to take on a stranger. The possibility of putting together a pickup group from others who may aslo have followed your path to get to that zone is remote, and becomes even more remote the further you go into the planes.<br>
<br>
It is reasonable for players to be levelling in first tier planes till 63-64. There's some challenging mobs even to those levels. So it's not unreasonable that they be rewarded for it. I don't think much in those planes should drop stuff for 65 spells though, aside perhaps the toughest named mobs in those zones.<br>
<br>
Tier 2 planes are more challenging than tier 1, but still not hugely so. Still, they are generally better for the 62+ crowd (well, anyone really, but in my experience, nobody under level 60 performs well in Valor or Storms). Still wouldn't expect 65 spells being terribly common, basiclly dropping from bigger named mobs. But I would expect to see more ethereal and spectral parchments. Risk is greater, rewards should be greater.<br>
<br>
I haven't been to HoH, Bastion of Thunder, or beyond, so I can't really comment on them. I'll just say that given the demand there is for parchments and the everpresent chance of getting duplicate spells from a turn in, making the parchments tediously rare was a poor decision.<br>
